quran[24]{c,v,t,f}:
  51,55,"And remind (by preaching the Qur’ân, O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم), for verily, the reminding profits the believers."
  51,56,"And I (Allâh) created not the jinn and mankind except that they should worship Me (Alone)."
  51,57,"I seek not any provision from them (i.e. provision for themselves or for My creatures) nor do I ask that they should feed Me (i.e. feed themselves or My creatures)."
  52,46,"The Day when their plotting shall not avail them at all nor will they be helped (i.e. they will receive their torment in Hell)."
  52,47,"And verily, for those who do wrong, there is another punishment (i.e. the torment in this world and in their graves){1} before this; but most of them know not. (Tafsir At-Tabarî).",footnotes:1:[{52:47} See the footnote (B) of {6:93}.]
  52,48,"So wait patiently (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) for the Decision of your Lord, for verily, you are under Our Eyes{1}; and glorify the Praises of your Lord when you get up from sleep.",footnotes:1:[{52:48} See the footnote of {3:73}.]
  53,40,"And that his deeds will be seen."
  53,41,"Then he will be recompensed with a full and the best recompense.{1}",footnotes:1:[{53:41} See the footnote (A) of {6:61}.]
  53,42,"And that to your Lord (Allâh) is the End (Return of everything)."
  54,31,"Verily, We sent against them a single Saihah (torment - awful cry), and they became like the stubble of a fold-builder."
  54,32,"And indeed, We have made the Qur’ân easy to understand and remember; then is there any that will remember (or receive admonition)?"
  54,33,"The people of Lût (Lot) belied the warnings."
  55,25,"Then which of the Blessings of your Lord will you both (jinn and men) deny?"
  55,26,"Whatsoever is on it (the earth) will perish."
  55,27,"And the Face of your Lord full of Majesty and Honour will remain forever."
  56,16,"Reclining thereon, face to face."
  56,17,"Immortal boys will go around them (serving),"
  56,18,"With cups, and jugs, and a glass of flowing wine,"
  57,7,"Believe in Allâh and His Messenger (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم), and spend of that whereof He has made you trustees.{1} And such of you as believe and spend (in Allâh’s Way), theirs will be a great reward.",footnotes:1:[{57:7} See the footnote of {4:37}.]
  57,8,"And what is the matter with you that you believe not in Allâh! While the Messenger (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) invites you to believe in your Lord (Allâh); and He (Allâh) has indeed taken your covenant, if you are real believers."
  57,9,"It is He Who sends down manifest Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.) to His slave (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) that He may bring you out from darkness into light. And verily, Allâh is to you full of kindness, Most Merciful."
  58,1,"Indeed Allâh has heard the statement of her (Khaulah bint Tha‘labah) that disputes with you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) concerning her husband (Aus bin As-Sâmit), and complains to Allâh. And Allâh hears the argument between you both. Verily, Allâh is All-Hearer, All-Seer."
  58,2,"Those among you who make their wives unlawful to them by (Zihâr الظهار){1} (i.e. by saying to them ",footnotes:1:[{58:2} Az-Zihâr الظهار is the saying of a husband to his wife: You are to me like the back of my mother (i.e. unlawful for me to approach).]
  58,3,"And those who make unlawful to them their wives by Zihâr and wish to free themselves from what they uttered, (the penalty) in that case is the freeing of a slave before they touch each other. That is an admonition to you (so that you may not repeat such an ill thing). And Allâh is All-Aware of what you do."